{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require bus companies to use only zero emission or hybrid buses by 2030",
        "additional_details": "I ask that the UK government requires bus companies across England to use only zero emission single decker buses and zero emission/hybrid double decker buses by 2030 at the absolute latest. This should help us to meet a target of zero emissions by 2050, which many scientists argue is absolutely necessary to ensure a future for our planet (B).\r\n(A): TfL website \r\n(B): https://amp.theguardian.com/environment/2019/may/02/do-it-now-uk-must-set-zero-carbon-target-for-2050-say-official-advisers",
        "background": "Transport for London has already announced that from 2020, all single decker buses entering service will be zero emission (electric or hydrogen) - (A). As Parliament has declared a \u2018climate emergency\u2019, it is only right that we set ambitious goals for clean buses across the whole of England.",
